title: cuisine-dim-sum
caption: Dim Sum
tags: cuisine
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Cantonese tradition of small dishes served alongside tea (yum cha).  Classics include har gow (shrimp dumplings in a translucent rice-starch wrapper), siu mai (pork and prawn), cheung fun (rice noodle rolls), and char siu bao (BBQ pork buns, either steamed or baked).
